'''PhotoIreland Foundation''' is the [[Ireland|Irish]] organisation which organises the annual PhotoIreland Festival, and runs the exhibition space, book shop, and library called The Library Project in [[Temple Bar, Dublin]].
==Description== PhotoIreland was founded by Ángel Luis González in 2009 with the aim of promoting photography in Ireland. They held the first annual month long PhotoIreland Festival in 2010.<ref name="Morley">{{cite web|last1=Morley|first1=Madeleine|title=The Library Project, Dublin|url=https://magculture.com/the-library-project-dublin/|website=Magculture|publisher=Magculture|accessdate=7 March 2018|date=11 September 2015}}</ref>
==The Library Project== The Library Project is a bookshop specialising in books on photography, a library and a gallery space. The library contains [[photo-book]]s, [[fanzine]]s and [[magazine]]s relating to photography.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Library Project|url=https://www.discoverireland.ie/Arts-Culture-Heritage/the-library-project/92385|website=Discover Ireland|accessdate=7 March 2018}}</ref> It was founded as part of the PhotoIreland Foundation's work in 2011 with the aim of improving access to specialised photography printed material for purchase or study.<ref name="Morley" /> It was initially part of a book fair and a collection of material that arose from that event in 2011. PhotoIreland Foundation and The Library Project found permanent premises in Temple Bar in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Davidson|first1=Eric|title=Inside the Library Project|url=http://districtmagazine.ie/feature/inside-the-library-project/|website=District Magazine|accessdate=7 March 2018|date=16 February 2015}}</ref><ref name="Carson">{{cite web|last1=Carson|first1=Emily|title=Shhhh! Inside The Library Project|url=http://www.totallydublin.ie/arts-culture/arts-culture-features/shhhh-inside-the-library-project/|website=Totally Dublin|accessdate=7 March 2018|date=4 September 2014}}</ref>
